    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_12_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_12",
      "description": "Offered is an exceptional 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in 90s JDM engineering. This example features the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, exhibiting perfect compression across all rotor faces. The factory vacuum routing is pristine, ensuring a linear power delivery and seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi turbos. The chassis remains structurally flawless, retaining its original double-wishbone suspension geometry and aluminum components for telepathic handling. Power is delivered through a crisp five-speed manual transmission to a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. This is a survivor-grade vehicle with an unmolested interior and factory-spec cooling system, representing the pinnacle of the FD chassis's lightweight, 50/50 weight distribution philosophy.",
